  "original_title": "SL to request Japan to initiate dialogue with creditors",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "SL to request Japan to initiate dialogue with creditors",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka is likely to request Japan to initiate a dialogue with Sri Lanka\u2019s creditors including China and India, foreign media reported yesterday.",
        "The report quoted President Ranil Wickremesinghe of making such a remark.",
        "It was also reported that President Wickremesinghe was scheduled to travel to Tokyo next month to hold talks with Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida but a spokesman from the President\u2019s office told Daily Mirror that he will fly to Japan to attend the funeral of former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe.",
        "Meanwhile Mr.Wickremesnghe earlier on Tuesday made a somewhat similar remark when he said Sri Lanka will have to talk to Japan on how Sri Lanka could come out of woods. He stressed the need for having a dialogue with top donors including India and China. He also said talks will go on with the IMF in order to finalize a staff level agreement. In addition the President revealed that LAZARD one of the advisors on Sri Lanka\u2019s debt resettlement had prepared a distress sustainability plan. (Yohan Perera)"
      ],
